{
  "texts": [
    "To quantify the depth of the central flux depression, we added a circular Gaussian to act as a \"floor\" in the crescent center.",
    "We also added an additional asymmetric Gaussian pinned to the inner edge of the crescent at the point where the width is largest, inspired by the model from Benkevitch et al. (2016).",
    "The overall \"image\" was then smoothed with a Gaussian kernel, and two additional \"nuisance\" asymmetric Gaussian components were introduced to help model diffuse emission near the ring.",
    "A cartoon describing each model component is shown in The main difference between the Hybrid Themage and the xs-ringauss model construction is in the treatment of the diffuse emission.",
    "The xs-ringauss model used a pair of asymmetric Gaussians to help model any non-ring emission, and the Hybrid Themage used the adaptive raster components."
  ]
}